Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
To tie your shoes, you must first grab the laces and make two loops (one per shoelace). Then, you cross the two loops and tuck one of them under the other while holding one. Then you pull the laces tight to finish tieing your shoe. You can repeat the process to make sure the knots will not come undone.